臺灣新編戲曲專題研究                     SEMINAR ON INNOVATIVE TAIWANESE OPERA


  	一、教學目標：
本課程探討台灣五十年來的新編戲曲劇目，包括從創作思維、劇本導讀、導演技法、角色行當、舞臺設計、音樂設計為教學重點。
二、教學內容：
本課程係為戲劇與音樂類合授課程，以台灣劇團的新編戲曲劇目為主，並以編劇、導演、演員、編曲及舞美，為探討內容。並且以台灣三大劇種及其代表作品：崑劇《梁山伯與祝英台》、《李香君》、京劇《閻羅夢》《快雪時晴》《王有道休妻》、豫劇《慈禧與珍妃》《花嫁巫娘》共七個劇目，分別闡述。
I. Course Objectives: 
For 50 years, Taiwanese newly organized opera has already reached a huge achievement. This course will introduce the essential spirit of Taiwanese consciousness and related theories on the themes of scripts, directing skills, roles, music directing, and stage design.
II. Course Description: 
This course is interdisciplinary of two different subjects: drama and music. The framework of the course is the repertoire of Taiwanese newly organized Xiqu and the discussion on scripts, directing, actors/actresses, music and dance. Three major dramatic genres will be included: 1) Kunju: Liang & Zhu: The Butterfly Lovers, and Lee Xiang-jun. 2) Peking Opera: Journey through Hell, Sunlight after Snowfall, and Mr. Goodman Dumps His Wife. 3) Bangzi Opera: Empress Dowager Cixi and Imperial Consort Zhen, and The Sorceress Bride.



